From 6b5a08101838dda7d091017355ed5c7277eeb2a1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Elias Ellison <elias.ellison@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 01:36:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] [inductor] Scalar-accumulator reduction codegen +
 online-softmax scalar path (prerequisite for scalar-acc / online-softmax PRs)

Minimal scaffolding carved from the June 2026 mega-commit 97385fb3273:
- config.triton.scalar_reduction_accumulators flag
- the reduction() codegen rewrite in codegen/triton.py adding the scalar
  accumulator path for simple associative reductions and the scalar
  online-softmax path (plus the online_softmax_cross_entropy codegen it
  is interleaved with)
- the MAX_R0_BLOCK scalar-acc branch in runtime/triton_heuristics.py

The reduction() rewrite is a single interleaved method and is carried whole;
it is the shared base for both scalar-acc and online-softmax fast-combine.

written with claude code
