Date: Wed, 3 Jun 2026 22:30:01 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] [inductor] Gate scalar_acc on num_load <= 4 (fix 14-22%
 regressions)

Scalar reduction accumulators add cross-warp tl.sum + shared memory
barrier per iteration. For bandwidth-bound kernels with many loads
(num_load >= 9), the vector accumulator costs only 4-8 registers
(XBLOCK=1) so there's no register pressure to save, but the sync
cost dominates.

Gate: only enable scalar_acc when num_load <= 4.
- Beneficial cases (online softmax): num_load=1-2, still enabled
- Regressing cases (BN backward): num_load=9-12, now disabled
- Clean separation with generous margin

