From 4a2db251d12c290dadd5a3484a9fa96e051b060d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Elias Ellison <elias.ellison@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 15:59:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] [inductor] Ungate scalar-acc configs from CD + raise
 rnumel ceiling (genai SoftmaxForward default 3541->1905us)

The scalar-accumulator / large-R0_BLOCK reduction knowledge in
_reduction_configs was gated on coordinate_descent_tuning and windowed to
8192 <= rnumel <= 131072. Both were calibrated against the pre-fast-combine
online-softmax cost model (before a26fc2c8bf4): the good configs were
excluded from DEFAULT autotune by construction, and even CD's starting
window excluded rnumel=262144 (it only got there by walking).

Changes, behind a new default-on flag scalar_acc_configs_without_cd
(TORCHINDUCTOR_SCALAR_ACC_CONFIGS_WITHOUT_CD):
- has_scalar_acc is now a kernel property (loads_and_red <= 3 or
  has_online_softmax), no CD term.
- rnumel ceiling re-measured on B200 and raised 131072 -> 1048576:
  large-R0 wins at 512K (sum 1478->613us, softmax 3733->1936us) and at
  1M (softmax 3899->2149us); split heuristics own small-x cases and the
  post-split inner kernel has much smaller rnumel, so no collision.
- Two extra candidates (XBLOCK=1, R0=8192/4 warps and R0=16384/8 warps)
  added for scalar-acc kernels in this window: the ReductionHint.INNER
  path returns a single config, so without candidates the default
  autotune could never reach the measured optimum (CD converges to the
  same configs).

genai suite (B200, default autotune before -> after; CD unchanged within
noise):
  SoftmaxForward/000        3541 -> 1905us  (CD 1914)
  SoftmaxBackward/000       3526 -> 1435us  (CD 1402)
  CrossEntropyForward/000   1969 ->  709us  (CD 746 -> 708)
  CrossEntropyBackward/000  1977 ->  717us  (CD 747 -> 717)
  amax_sum_sum_6fd07d12d98a (hf_distillgpt2) default 971 -> 543us.
Sentinels (sum_0becf9609ad7, sum_011e69da166d, amax_sum_0561785713ab,
mean_var_mean_3c4ea6d8f342) unchanged in both default and CD modes.

